  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6593.82 sitting between the massive negative gamma wall at 6500 (-4.46B) and positive gamma at 6600 (+4.32B), dealers are currently in neutral hedging mode but poised for action. The PIN regime suggests dealers will aggressively sell any push toward 6600 and provide strong support if we drift toward 6500, creating a tight trading range. The gex_surge event with 88% 1-min change indicates fresh positioning that should amplify these hedging flows.\n\nKey levels: 6500 support (dealers buy heavily) and 6600 resistance (dealers sell), with the 6695 flip strike as the breakout threshold where regime dynamics reverse.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect choppy action trapped between 6500-6600 with strong dealer flows at both boundaries.",
